agent-mesh — NOTICE
===================

This project is a clean-room showcase. It contains only original code and
public, open-source dependencies. It is released under the MIT License (see the
LICENSE file).

PURPOSE
-------
agent-mesh is inspired by, but shares NO source code, data, prompts, schemas,
database contents, configuration, or model weights with, any private or
proprietary project. The designs here are generic reimplementations of
widely-known, publicly-documented patterns (vector memory over a database;
file-format conversion; logging and cost accounting for model calls). Any
resemblance to a private system is at the level of general engineering ideas,
not implementation.

COMPONENTS
----------
  memory-server
      A generic vector-memory store (FAISS for similarity search + SQLite as
      the system of record) exposed over the Model Context Protocol. It does
      not reproduce any proprietary memory system's code, schema, embeddings,
      or stored data.

  file-bridge-server
      A thin MCP wrapper around a pluggable file-conversion interface. It ships
      only generic reference converters built on public libraries (a
      pure-Python Markdown-to-text converter, PyMuPDF for PDF text extraction,
      and pandoc for document formats). Any private or proprietary conversion
      logic can be added behind the documented `Converter` interface WITHOUT
      modifying this public repository and WITHOUT being distributed with it.

  prompt-audit-server
      A generic logger for LLM call metadata — token counts, latency, and a
      transparent, heuristic quality score — backed by SQLite, with simple
      statistics and a configurable notional cost table. It contains no
      proprietary prompts, evaluation rubrics, or pricing data.

